com.intel.fightclub.dialog.tokens

Interface ExpirationToken

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    AudioFocusToken, CuiToken, LpalToken, SpeechToken

    public interface ExpirationToken
    Interface for a token that expires over time. Renewing the token will extend its expiration time. This is useful for keeping track of time sensitive events in the CUI.

    • Method Detail

      • expire

        void expire(boolean notify)
        Explicitly expire the token.
        Parameters:
        notify - If true, the registered ExpirationListener's onExpired method will be called.

      • getRemainingTimeMillis

        long getRemainingTimeMillis()
        Returns:
        The remaining time (in milliseconds) before this token will expire.

      • isExpired

        boolean isExpired()
        Returns:
        True if the token has expired and false otherwise.

      • renew

        boolean renew()
        Renews the token thus extending its lifetime. If the token is expired, then this method should un-expire the token and restart the timeout.
        Returns:
        True if the token was successfully renewed and the timer was reset accordingly.

      • renew

        boolean renew(long newTimeoutMillis)
        Renews the token and extends its lifetime by the provided amount. If the token is expired, then this method should un-expire the token and restart the timeout.
        Parameters:
        newTimeoutMillis - The expiration time (in milliseconds) to use.
        Returns:
        True if the token was successfully renewed and the timer was reset accordingly.

      • reset

        void reset()
        Resets the token to its original state. This is the equivalent of creating a new token instance.

      • setExpirationListener

        void setExpirationListener(@NonNull
                           ExpirationListener listener)
        Sets a listener that receives expiration events.
        Parameters:
        listener - The listener to register.
        Throws:
        java.lang.NullPointerException - Thrown if the listener is null.
